309    private function __construct(string $amount, string $currencyCode, PaymentMethodType $paymentMethodType)
310    {
311        $this->fundingWithdrawals = new ArrayCollection();
312        $this->currencyCode = $currencyCode;
313        $maximumAmount = self::maximumAmount($paymentMethodType);
314
315        if (
316            bccomp($amount, (string)self::MINUMUM_AMOUNT, 2) === -1 ||
317            bccomp($amount, (string)$maximumAmount, 2) === 1
318        ) {
319            throw new \UnexpectedValueException(sprintf(
320                'Amount must be %d-%d %s',
321                self::MINUMUM_AMOUNT,
322                $maximumAmount,
323                $this->currencyCode,
324            ));
325        }
326
327        $this->amount = $amount;
328        $this->paymentMethodType = $paymentMethodType;
329    }

331    public static function fromApiModel(DonationCreate $donationData, Campaign $campaign): Donation
332    {
333        $psp = $donationData->psp;
334        assert($psp === 'stripe');
335
336        $donation = new self(
337            $donationData->donationAmount,
338            $donationData->currencyCode,
339            $donationData->paymentMethodType,
340        );
341
342        $donation->setPsp($psp);
343        $donation->setUuid(Uuid::uuid4());
344        $donation->setCampaign($campaign); // Charity & match expectation determined implicitly from this
345
346        $donation->setGiftAid($donationData->giftAid);
347        // `DonationCreate` doesn't support a distinct property yet & we only ask once about GA.
348        $donation->setTipGiftAid($donationData->giftAid);
349        $donation->setTbgShouldProcessGiftAid($campaign->getCharity()->isTbgClaimingGiftAid());
350
351        $donation->setCharityComms($donationData->optInCharityEmail);
352        $donation->setChampionComms($donationData->optInChampionEmail);
353        $donation->setPspCustomerId($donationData->pspCustomerId);
354        $donation->setTbgComms($donationData->optInTbgEmail);
355        $donation->setDonorFirstName($donationData->firstName);
356        $donation->setDonorLastName($donationData->lastName);
357        $donation->setDonorEmailAddress($donationData->emailAddress);
358
359        if (!empty($donationData->countryCode)) {
360            $donation->setDonorCountryCode($donationData->countryCode);
361        }
362
363        if (isset($donationData->feeCoverAmount)) {
364            $donation->setFeeCoverAmount($donationData->feeCoverAmount);
365        }
366
367        if (isset($donationData->tipAmount)) {
368            $donation->setTipAmount($donationData->tipAmount);
369        }
370
371        return $donation;
372    }
373
374    private static function maximumAmount(PaymentMethodType $paymentMethodType): int
375    {
376        return match ($paymentMethodType) {
377            PaymentMethodType::CustomerBalance => self::MAXIMUM_CUSTOMER_BALANCE_DONATION,
378            PaymentMethodType::Card => self::MAXIMUM_CARD_DONATION,
379        };
380    }
381
382    public function __toString(): string
383    {
384        // if we're in __toString then probably something has already gone wrong, and we don't want to allow
385        // any more crashes during the logging process.
386        try {
387            $charityName = $this->getCampaign()->getCharity()->getName();
388        } catch (\Throwable $t) {
389            // perhaps the charity was never pulled from Salesforce into our database, in which case we might
390            // have a TypeError trying to get a string name from it.
391            $charityName = "[pending charity threw " . get_class($t) . "]";
392        }
393        return "Donation {$this->getUuid()} to $charityName";
394    }
395
396    /*
397     * In contrast to __toString, this is used when creating a payment intent. If we can't find the charity name
398     * then we should let the process of making the intent and registering the donation crash.
399     */
400    public function getDescription(): string
401    {
402        $charityName = $this->getCampaign()->getCharity()->getName();
403        return "Donation {$this->getUuid()} to $charityName";
404    }

406    /**
407     * @ORM\PreUpdate Check that the amount is never changed
408     * @param PreUpdateEventArgs $args
409     * @throws \LogicException if amount is changed
410     */
411    public function preUpdate(PreUpdateEventArgs $args): void
412    {
413        if (!$args->hasChangedField('amount')) {
414            return;
415        }
416
417        if ($args->getOldValue('amount') !== $args->getNewValue('amount')) {
418            throw new \LogicException('Amount may not be changed after a donation is created');
419        }
420    }

422    public function replaceNullPaymentMethodTypeWithCard(): void
423    {
424        if ($this->paymentMethodType !== null) {
425            throw new \Exception('Should only be called when payment method type is null');
426        }
427        $this->paymentMethodType = PaymentMethodType::Card;
428    }

430    /**
431     * @return array A json encode-ready array representation of the donation, for sending to Salesforce.
432     */
433    public function toHookModel(): array
434    {
435        $data = $this->toApiModel();
436
437        // MAT-234 - remove dubious patterns from email for now so records can save in SF.
438        if ($data['emailAddress'] !== null && str_contains($data['emailAddress'], ';;')) {
439            $data['emailAddress'] = str_replace(';;', '', $data['emailAddress']);
440        }
441
442        $data['updatedTime'] = $this->getUpdatedDate()->format(DateTimeInterface::ATOM);
443        $data['amountMatchedByChampionFunds'] = (float) $this->getConfirmedChampionWithdrawalTotal();
444        $data['amountMatchedByPledges'] = (float) $this->getConfirmedPledgeWithdrawalTotal();
445        $data['originalPspFee'] = (float) $this->getOriginalPspFee();
446        $data['refundedTime'] = $this->refundedAt?->format(DateTimeInterface::ATOM);
447
448        unset(
449            $data['charityName'],
450            $data['donationId'],
451            $data['matchReservedAmount'],
452            $data['matchedAmount'],
453            $data['cardBrand'],
454            $data['cardCountry'],
455        );
456
457        return $data;
458    }

460    public function toApiModel(): array
461    {

467            'charityName' => $this->getCampaign()->getCharity()->getName(),
468            'countryCode' => $this->getDonorCountryCode(),
469            'collectedTime' => $this->getCollectedAt()?->format(DateTimeInterface::ATOM),
470            'createdTime' => $this->getCreatedDate()->format(DateTimeInterface::ATOM),
471            'currencyCode' => $this->getCurrencyCode(),
472            'donationAmount' => (float) $this->getAmount(),
473            'donationId' => $this->getUuid(),
474            'donationMatched' => $this->getCampaign()->isMatched(),
475            'emailAddress' => $this->getDonorEmailAddress(),
476            'feeCoverAmount' => (float) $this->getFeeCoverAmount(),
477            'firstName' => $this->getDonorFirstName(true),
478            'giftAid' => $this->hasGiftAid(),
479            'homeAddress' => $this->getDonorHomeAddressLine1(),
480            'homePostcode' => $this->getDonorHomePostcode(),
481            'lastName' => $this->getDonorLastName(true),
482            'matchedAmount' => $this->getDonationStatus()->isSuccessful() ? (float) $this->getFundingWithdrawalTotal() : 0,
483            'matchReservedAmount' => 0,
484            'optInCharityEmail' => $this->getCharityComms(),

487            'projectId' => $this->getCampaign()->getSalesforceId(),

489            'pspCustomerId' => $this->getPspCustomerId(),

516            throw new \Exception('Donation::cancelled must be used to cancel');
517        }

520    }

725            return '0.0';
726        }

731            if ($fundingWithdrawal->getCampaignFunding()->getFund() instanceof ChampionFund) {
732                $withdrawalTotal = bcadd($withdrawalTotal, $fundingWithdrawal->getAmount(), 2);
733            }
734        }
735
736        return $withdrawalTotal;
737    }

862    public function setTipAmount(string $tipAmount): void
863    {
864        /** @psalm-var numeric-string $tipAmount */
865        if (
866            $this->paymentMethodType === PaymentMethodType::CustomerBalance &&
867            bccomp($tipAmount, '0', 2) !== 0
868        ) {
869            // We would have accepted a tip at the time the customer balance was created, so we don't take a second
870            // tip as part of the donation.
871            throw new \UnexpectedValueException('A Customer Balance Donation may not include a tip');
872        }
873
874        $max = self::MAXIMUM_CARD_DONATION;
875
876        if (bccomp($tipAmount, (string)(self::MAXIMUM_CARD_DONATION), 2) === 1) {
877            throw new \UnexpectedValueException(sprintf(
878                'Tip amount must not exceed %d %s',
879                $max,
880                $this->currencyCode,
881            ));
882        }
883
884        if (bccomp($tipAmount, '0', 2) === -1) {
885            throw new \UnexpectedValueException('Tip amount must not be negative');
886        }
887
888        $this->tipAmount = $tipAmount;
889    }

946    /**
947     * @return int      The amount of the total donation, in cents/pence/..., which is to be excluded
948     *                  from payout to the charity. This is the sum of
949     *                  (a) any part of that amount which was a tip to the Big Give;
950     *                  (b) fees on the remaining donation amount; and
951     *                  (c) VAT on fees where applicable.
952     *                  It does not include separately sourced funds like matching or
953     *                  Gift Aid.
954     */
955    public function getAmountToDeductFractional(): int
956    {
957        $amountToDeduct = bcadd($this->getTipAmount(), $this->getCharityFeeGross(), 2);
958
959        return (int) bcmul('100', $amountToDeduct, 2);
960    }
961
962    /**
963     * @return int      The amount of the core donation, in pence/cents/..., which is to be paid out
964     *                  to the charity. This is the amount paid by the donor minus
965     *                  (a) any part of that amount which was a tip to the Big Give;
966     *                  (b) fees on the remaining donation amount; and
967     *                  (c) VAT on fees where applicable.
968     *                  It does not include separately sourced funds like matching or
969     *                  Gift Aid.
970     *
971     *                  This is just used in unit tests to validate we haven't broken anything now.
972     *                  Note that because `getAmountToDeductFractional()` takes off the tip amount and
973     *                  `getAmount()` relates to core amount, we must re-add the tip here to get a
974     *                  correct answer.
975     */
976    public function getAmountForCharityFractional(): int
977    {
978        $amountFractional = (int) bcmul('100', $this->getAmount(), 2);
979        return $amountFractional +
980            $this->getFeeCoverAmountFractional() +
981            $this->getTipAmountFractional() -
982            $this->getAmountToDeductFractional();
983    }
984
985    /**
986     * @return int  Full amount, including any tip or fee cover, in pence/cents/...
987     */
988    public function getAmountFractionalIncTip(): int
989    {
990        $coreAmountFractional = (int) bcmul('100', $this->getAmount(), 2);
991
992        return
993            $coreAmountFractional +
994            $this->getFeeCoverAmountFractional() +
995            $this->getTipAmountFractional();
996    }

1129    public function getPaymentMethodType(): ?PaymentMethodType
1130    {
1131        return $this->paymentMethodType;
1132    }
1133
1134    /**
1135     * We want to ensure each Payment Intent is set up to be settled a specific way, so
1136     * we get this from an on-create property of the Donation instead of using
1137     * `automatic_payment_methods`.
1138     * "card" includes wallets and is the method for the vast majority of donations.
1139     * "customer_balance" is used when a previous bank transfer means a donor already
1140     * has credits to use for platform charities, *and* for Big Give tips set up when
1141     * preparing to make a bank transfer. In the latter case we rely on
1142     * `payment_method_options` to allow the PI to be created even though there aren't
1143     * yet sufficient funds.
1144     */
1145    public function getStripeMethodProperties(): array
1146    {
1147        $properties = match ($this->paymentMethodType) {
1148            PaymentMethodType::CustomerBalance => [
1149                'payment_method_types' => ['customer_balance'],
1150            ],
1151            PaymentMethodType::Card => [
1152                // in this case we want to use the Stripe Payment Element, so we can't specify card explicitly, we
1153                // need to turn on automatic methods instead and let the element decide what methods to show.
1154                'automatic_payment_methods' => [
1155                    'enabled' => true,
1156                    'allow_redirects' => 'never',
1157                ]
1158            ],
1159        };
1160
1161        if ($this->paymentMethodType === PaymentMethodType::CustomerBalance) {
1162            if ($this->currencyCode !== 'GBP') {
1163                throw new \UnexpectedValueException('Customer balance payments only supported for GBP');
1164            }
1165
1166            $properties['payment_method_data'] = [
1167                'type' => PaymentMethodType::CustomerBalance->value,
1168            ];
1169
1170            $properties['payment_method_options'] = [
1171                'customer_balance' => [
1172                    'funding_type' => 'bank_transfer',
1173                    'bank_transfer' => [
1174                        'type' => 'gb_bank_transfer',
1175                    ],
1176                ],
1177            ];
1178        }
1179
1180        return $properties;
1181    }
1182
1183    /**
1184     * This isn't supported for "customer_balance" Payment Intents, and is also not
1185     * really needed for them because the fee is fixed at the lowest level and there
1186     * is no new donor bank transaction, so no statement ref to consider.
1187     *
1188     * An important side effect to keep in mind is that this means payout timing for
1189     * donations funded by bank transfer / customer balance is dictated by the platform
1190     * (Big Give) Stripe settings, *not* those of the receiving charity's connected
1191     * account. This means we cannot currently add a delay, so depending on the day of the
1192     * week it's received, a donation could be paid out to the charity almost immediately.
1193     * This may necessitate us having a different refund policy for donations via credit –
1194     * to be discussed further in early/mid 2023.
1195     *
1196     * @link https://stripe.com/docs/payments/connected-accounts
1197     * @link https://stripe.com/docs/connect/destination-charges#settlement-merchant
1198     */
1199    public function getStripeOnBehalfOfProperties(): array
1200    {
1201        if ($this->paymentMethodType === PaymentMethodType::Card) {
1202            return ['on_behalf_of' => $this->getCampaign()->getCharity()->getStripeAccountId()];
1203        }
1204
1205        return [];
1206    }
1207
